            "description": "<p><figure class=\"getty-figure\" data-type=\"getty-image\"><picture> <img src=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2189068007/image_2189068007.jpg?io=getty-c-w750\" alt=\"Percentage sign cut in half by scissor\" data-id=\"2189068007\" data-type=\"getty-image\" width=\"1536px\" height=\"878px\" srcset=\"https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2189068007/image_2189068007.jpg?io=getty-c-w1536 1536w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2189068007/image_2189068007.jpg?io=getty-c-w1280 1280w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2189068007/image_2189068007.jpg?io=getty-c-w1080 1080w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2189068007/image_2189068007.jpg?io=getty-c-w750 750w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2189068007/image_2189068007.jpg?io=getty-c-w640 640w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2189068007/image_2189068007.jpg?io=getty-c-w480 480w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2189068007/image_2189068007.jpg?io=getty-c-w320 320w, https://static.seekingalpha.com/cdn/s3/uploads/getty_images/2189068007/image_2189068007.jpg?io=getty-c-w240 240w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 36px), (max-width: 1024px) calc(100vw - 132px), (max-width: 1200px) calc(66.6vw - 72px), 600px\" fetchpriority=\"high\"> </picture><figcaption><p class=\"item-caption\"> </p> <p class=\"item-credits\">J Studios</p></figcaption></figure></p> <div class=\"inline_ad_placeholder\"></div> <p>I rate <strong>Crown Castle Inc.</strong> (NYSE:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/CCI\" class=\"ticker-link\">CCI</a>) a Sell, for income-focused investors interested in real estate investment trusts (REITs). CCI <a href=\"https://investor.crowncastle.com/news-releases/news-release-details/crown-castle-announces-agreement-sell-fiber-segment-eqt-and-zayo\" rel=\"noopener\">recently announced</a> a -32% dividend cut starting in Q2, combined with a $3 billion stock buyback and sale of</p>",
